rComments: Really nice guy! Super chill and funny. I found his midterm easier than his final but he's really fair. Having labs every week is kinda a pain (especially when you're writing them), but it's a fun course to take. It was my lowest grade but one of my funnest classes. Good times! If you're reading this, thanks Bush!

Make sure to check all NFL players and teams and their quarterbacks and also make sure to ask when his birthday is before you do the midterms and exam.   How is this relevant to organic chemistry? I don't know, but you're welcome!

Alex was a PhD candidat at the time I took this class, and he did a pretty good job! Lab manual was nice and clear, not too many mistakes; grading criteria was clear, made the lab report writing more efficient. His midterm and final exam were fair. Your grade depends largely on your TA, since they mark your lab reports.

Labs are clear and there's plenty of time to do them.   Only qualm is that you have to know your calculations for the midterm as he gives no carrry-through marks.   Know your labs, manual, and lab questions inside out as occasionally he'll pull some obscure material from the lab question that wasn't directly covered in the lab.

He is a good Lab Coordinator. Does not waste time giving you a big presentation at the beginning of each lab - he just lets you get on with it. The midterm for his course was okay, you definitely need to know your work very well. His laid back attitude really makes him approachable and he is very funny. Overall I was happy with him.
Pretty much the most laid back prof you will ever have, his midterm was fair and quite funny.  The lab manual is kinda confusing, but he answers emailed questions about it very fast (within the day).
